EDUCATIONAL
WORK

“School educates not by knowledge, but by example and actions.”

EDUCATIONAL WORK

— a system of activities and measures aimed at developing students’ values, communication culture, responsibility, and personal growth.

1.

Class Hours and
Thematic Events

The school regularly holds class hours and educational events aimed at fostering students’ spiritual and moral values, communication culture, safe behavior, and healthy lifestyle. The topics cover current issues of modern life: patriotism, tolerance, ecology, crime prevention, personal safety, and leadership development.

2.

Clubs, Sections, and Creative Studios

To develop children’s abilities and talents, the school offers various interest-based groups:
sports sections (football, athletics, volleyball, etc.);
creative clubs (theater studio, choreography);
intellectual clubs and subject circles (mathematics, robotics, English club).

These programs help each child find their calling and showcase their best qualities.

3.

Patriotic and Spiritual-Moral Education

Special attention is given to cultivating patriotism, love for the homeland, and respect for Kazakhstan’s cultural traditions. Activities include events dedicated to national holidays, meetings with veterans, and excursions to museums and memorial sites. Spiritual-moral education is based on the values of respect, honesty, responsibility, friendship, and mutual assistance.

4.

School Educational System

The educational system of School-Gymnasium #1 is developed under the “Adal Azamat” program and is based on the principles of cooperation between teachers, parents, and students. It is aimed at:

developing a harmonious personality;
forming an active civic position;
promoting health culture and safe behavior;
supporting talented and initiative students.

Thanks to this systematic approach, the school’s educational work helps children become responsible, creative, and successful individuals.
